        <div class="cardtext">
            <p>The "Value of Property Stolen" quantifies the total monetary loss resulting from theft or criminal
                activities. It encompasses the collective worth of items unlawfully taken during specific incidents,
                providing a comprehensive measure of the economic impact of property crimes on individuals and
                communities.</p>
            <p>This refers to the total monetary worth of the property that has been unlawfully taken or removed by
                theft, burglary, robbery, or any other criminal activity. It includes the combined value of all items
                stolen during a specific incident or over a certain period. This value is typically determined by the
                original purchase price of the items, but it may also take into account factors such as depreciation,
                condition, and rarity.</p>
            <p>In addition to the original purchase price, other factors that may be considered when determining the
                value of property stolen include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>The condition of the item</li>
                <li>The rarity of the item</li>
                <li>The sentimental value of the item</li>
                <li>The replacement cost of the item</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
