            <p>Property Recovered</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cardtext">
            <p>This represents the monetary worth of stolen property that has been successfully retrieved by law
                enforcement agencies or individuals.Property recovery can occur through various means, including police
                investigations, raids, tips from the public, or the return of stolen items by the perpetrators
                themselves.</p>
            <p>The value of property recovered is an important indicator of the success of law enforcement efforts in
                combating theft. It can also be used to determine the extent to which victims of theft are able to
                recoup their losses. It can help to bring closure to victims, reduce their financial losses, and
                discourage future criminal activity. Additionally, recovered property can provide valuable evidence in
                criminal investigations.</p>
            <p>Here are some statistics on property recovery:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>According to the National Crime Victimization Survey (NCVS), the property recovery rate for thefts
                    from households was 22% in 2021.</li>
                <li>The recovery rate for motor vehicle theft was significantly higher, at 70% in 2021.</li>
                <li>The recovery rate varies depending on the type of property stolen, the jurisdiction in which the
                    theft occurred, and other factors.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Despite the challenges, law enforcement agencies continue to make significant efforts to recover stolen
                property. Advances in technology, such as DNA analysis and facial recognition software, have helped to
                improve recovery rates in recent years.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

